{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}

{% block content %}
  {% with summary = {"title": "Forecast", "headline": "Monte Carlo over " ~ when_done.daily_throughput_n_days ~ " days of throughput history. Drag the sliders to change the inputs."} %}
    {% include "_partials/metric_summary.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  <div class="forecast-grid">
    {# WWIBD - Date panel #}
    <section class="forecast-panel">
      <header class="forecast-panel-header">
        <h3>When will it be done?</h3>
        <p class="forecast-panel-sub">
          Given a backlog of <output id="items-output" for="items-slider">{{ items_slider }}</output> items,
          what dates do P50/P85/P95 land on?
        </p>
        <label class="forecast-slider-label" for="items-slider">
          Items
          <input id="items-slider"
                 type="range"
                 name="items"
                 min="1" max="500" step="1"
                 value="{{ items_slider }}"
                 hx-get="{{ ('/api/internal/forecast/when-done?workflow=' ~ contract.name ~ '&start=' ~ today_iso) | keep_filters }}"
                 hx-target="#forecast-when-done-chart-wrap"
                 hx-swap="outerHTML"
                 hx-trigger="input changed delay:100ms"
                 oninput="document.getElementById('items-output').textContent = this.value">
        </label>
      </header>
      {% with data = when_done, chart_height = 280 %}
        {% include "_partials/forecast_when_done_chart_fragment.html.jinja" %}
      {% endwith %}
    </section>

    {# WWIBD - How Many panel #}
    <section class="forecast-panel">
      <header class="forecast-panel-header">
        <h3>How many will be done?</h3>
        <p class="forecast-panel-sub">
          Over the next <output id="days-output" for="days-slider">{{ days_slider }}</output> days,
          P50/P85/P95 counts (a high-confidence FLOOR — "at least this many").
        </p>
        <label class="forecast-slider-label" for="days-slider">
          Days
          <input id="days-slider"
                 type="range"
                 name="days"
                 min="1" max="180" step="1"
                 value="{{ days_slider }}"
                 hx-get="{{ ('/api/internal/forecast/how-many?workflow=' ~ contract.name ~ '&start=' ~ today_iso) | keep_filters }}"
                 hx-target="#forecast-how-many-chart-wrap"
                 hx-swap="outerHTML"
                 hx-trigger="input changed delay:100ms"
                 oninput="document.getElementById('days-output').textContent = this.value">
        </label>
      </header>
      {% with data = how_many, chart_height = 280 %}
        {% include "_partials/forecast_how_many_chart_fragment.html.jinja" %}
      {% endwith %}
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="detail-extras">
    <h2>How to read this</h2>
    <p>
      Both panels run 10,000 Monte Carlo simulations against the
      historical daily-throughput distribution, sampling with
      replacement. The bars show how often each outcome occurred
      across the 10K runs.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>P85 by</strong> a date = "done by this date in
        85% of simulations" — the right number for a commitment.</li>
      <li><strong>P85 ≥</strong> a count = "at least this many
        finished in 85% of runs" — a high-confidence floor, not
        a likely expectation.</li>
      <li>Forecasts assume the future looks like the past. After
        a process, team, or scope change, the baseline window is
        a weaker predictor — rebaseline once enough new
        throughput data exists.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Possible next steps</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Commit on <strong>P85</strong>, plan on P50 (Vacanti).
        Reporting only P50 understates risk; reporting only P95
        leaves money on the table.</li>
      <li>If the distribution is wide, reduce variance before
        adding capacity — smaller batches, WIP limits and fewer
        in-progress threads move P85 down faster than more
        people do.</li>
      <li>If forecast and actuals drift apart, rebaseline the
        historical window rather than nudging the forecast by
        hand — the distribution carries the truth.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <a class="back-link" href="{{ ("/workflows/" ~ contract.name ~ "/") | keep_filters }}">← Back to dashboard</a>
{% endblock %}
